  "dateModified": "2026-04-27",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-27",
  "description": "Californication is recurrent across the modern pastoral apparatus; the medieval Christian church is its most thoroughly developed prior institutional form. What is recurrent: continuous calibration of inner life through pastoral relations and specific affective genres (acedia, spes, studiositas, curiositas). What is changed: the energetic substrate is inverted, latency has collapsed, protected interiors are gone, the contradictions metabolized differ.",
  "name": "The Ecclesial Recurrence",
